contextNodes.label: daytona-source
contextNodes.description: Cloud-native development environment platform providing isolated sandbox environments for code execution and development workflows. Offers CLI, web dashboard, and SDK interfaces for creating, managing, and accessing containerized development workspaces with snapshot capabilities.
contextNodes.stats: Go-based microservices architecture with React frontend, NestJS API service, and multi-language SDK support
contextNodes.purpose: Provides isolated, reproducible development environments as a service for software development teams and AI code generation workflows.

contextNodes.label: Developers
contextNodes.description: Software developers using CLI commands and SDK libraries to create sandbox environments, execute code, manage snapshots, and access development workspaces via SSH

contextNodes.label: AI Agents
contextNodes.description: AI systems and code generation tools using Python, TypeScript, Go, and Ruby SDKs to programmatically create sandboxes and execute generated code via REST APIs

contextNodes.label: Platform Administrators
contextNodes.description: Operations teams using React web dashboard to monitor sandbox usage metrics, manage organization settings, and configure platform resources via REST API calls

contextNodes.label: End Users
contextNodes.description: Application users accessing running applications deployed within sandbox environments through HTTP proxy service with SSL termination

contextNodes.label: Container Runtime
contextNodes.description: Docker/OCI container runtime providing sandbox isolation and execution via Docker API and containerd runtime interface for container lifecycle management

contextNodes.label: PostgreSQL Database
contextNodes.description: Primary relational database storing user accounts, organization data, and sandbox metadata accessed via SQL connections and PostgreSQL wire protocol

contextNodes.label: Redis Cache
contextNodes.description: In-memory data store providing session management, API response caching, and real-time data storage via Redis protocol and pub/sub messaging

contextNodes.label: Object Storage
contextNodes.description: S3-compatible storage service storing sandbox snapshots, filesystem backups, and persistent data via S3 API with multipart upload support

contextNodes.label: Observability Backend
contextNodes.description: External monitoring and logging systems receiving metrics, traces, and logs via OpenTelemetry protocol with OTLP gRPC and HTTP exporters

contextNodes.label: OAuth Providers
contextNodes.description: Third-party identity providers enabling user authentication and authorization via OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow and OpenID Connect protocols

moduleNodes.label: main-api-clients
moduleNodes.description: Auto-generated HTTP REST API client libraries for Python (sync/async), Go, Ruby, and TypeScript using OpenAPI Generator. Provides comprehensive API access with Pydantic models for request/response validation in Python clients. Implements async/await patterns in Python async client using aiohttp for non-blocking HTTP operations. Includes complete model definitions for all API entities like sandboxes, organizations, users, and audit logs.
moduleNodes.architecture: OpenAPI Generator creates language-specific HTTP clients with shared model definitions across sync and async Python variants. Python clients use Pydantic for JSON schema validation and aiohttp for async HTTP transport. Go client implements standard net/http patterns while Ruby client follows gem conventions. All clients share identical API surface with language-specific idioms.
